@@GNECROMANCER@@W

@@GHistory@@W
  The Necromancer tradition is older than the Psionicist academies that now
  claim jurisdiction over the mind arts. Before the academies there were the
  Entropy Scholars -- independent practitioners who studied decay and
  dissolution because they believed that understanding endings was essential
  to understanding existence. Over centuries their research drifted into
  practical application: sustaining the departed past their natural terminus,
  drawing on residual spiritual energy as a power source, weaponizing the
  same processes that unravel living systems. The academies branded them
  heretics; the Scholars noted that death itself cannot be outlawed by
  institutional consensus. Psionicists who return to study entropy rather
  than enhancement carry on that ancient, unsanctioned tradition.

Necromancers are entropy architects who weaponize decay, shadow, and attrition.
Their power grows as enemies lose tempo and control.

